Orders court proceedings to be scheduled or rescheduled for a date no sooner than 6/1/20, unless:
1. the proceeding will be conducted remotely;
2. the proceeding is necessary to preserve the right to due process of law;
3. the proceeding is for the purpose of obtaining emergency relief; or
4. the senior resident superior court judge, chief business court judge, or chief district court judge determines that the proceeding can be conducted under conditions that protect the health and safety of all participants.

Orders court proceedings to be scheduled or rescheduled for a date no sooner than 30 days from the issuance of the order, unless:
1. the proceeding will be conducted remotely;
2. the proceeding is necessary to preserve the right to due process of law;
3. the proceeding is for the purpose of obtaining emergency relief; or
4. the senior resident superior court judge, chief business court judge, or chief district court judge determines that the proceeding can be conducted under conditions that protect the health and safety of all participants.
